.TH CUSTODIA-ADMIN 1 "@DATE@" "Custodia @VERSION@" "Custodia Manual"
.SH NAME
custodia-admin \- administer a Custodia vault and certificate workflow
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY custodia-admin
.OP --server-url URL
.OP --cert FILE
.OP --key FILE
.OP --ca FILE
.I command
.RI [ arguments ...]
.YS
.SY custodia-admin
.B version
.YS
.SY custodia-admin
.B --version
.YS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B custodia-admin
is the operator CLI for Custodia. It talks to the vault API over mTLS,
performs metadata-only administration, exports and verifies audit material,
and orchestrates client certificate workflows.
.PP
When the admin certificate and key live under
.I /etc/custodia,
run the command as the restricted
.B custodia
service user, for example:
.PP
.EX
sudo -u custodia custodia-admin --server-url https://localhost:8443 \\
  --cert /etc/custodia/admin.crt \\
  --key /etc/custodia/admin.key \\
  --ca /etc/custodia/ca.crt version server
.EE
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B version
Print local build metadata and exit without contacting the server.
.TP
.B version server
Print server build metadata from
.BR /v1/version .
.TP
.B client create --client-id ID --mtls-subject SUBJECT
Register client metadata in the vault.
.TP
.B client csr --client-id ID --private-key-out FILE --csr-out FILE
Generate a local client mTLS private key and CSR.
.TP
.B client issue --client-id ID --out-dir DIR --signer-url URL
Register client metadata, generate local mTLS key/CSR, submit the CSR to
.BR custodia-signer (1),
extract the certificate, and create a local certificate bundle.
.TP
.B certificate sign --client-id ID --csr-file FILE
Submit a CSR to the signing service.
.TP
.B certificate extract --input FILE --certificate-out FILE
Extract a certificate PEM from signer JSON output.
.TP
.B certificate bundle --certificate FILE --private-key FILE --ca FILE --out FILE
Create a local ZIP bundle containing client mTLS material.
.TP
.B audit export
Export bounded audit metadata.
.TP
.B audit verify-export
Verify exported audit body/digest/count artifacts.
.TP
.B production check
Run production configuration checks from an environment file.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --server-url " URL"
Custodia API base URL.
.TP
.BI --cert " FILE"
Admin mTLS client certificate.
.TP
.BI --key " FILE"
Admin mTLS private key.
.TP
.BI --ca " FILE"
Custodia CA certificate.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_BASE_URL
Default API base URL.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_ADMIN_CERT
Default admin certificate path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_ADMIN_KEY
Default admin private key path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_CA_CERT
Default CA certificate path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_URL
Default signer URL for client certificate issue workflows.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/admin.crt
Default local admin mTLS certificate.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/admin.key
Default local admin mTLS private key. Keep readable only by root/custodia.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/ca.crt
Default Custodia CA certificate.
.TP
.I /var/log/custodia/
Default server and signer log directory for packaged installs.
.SH SECURITY NOTES
.B custodia-admin
must not handle secret plaintext, DEKs, recipient envelopes, or application
private encryption keys. It is an administrative metadata and certificate
workflow tool.
.PP
Prefer running commands that read
.I /etc/custodia/admin.key
as the
.B custodia
service user instead of unrestricted root.
.SH EXAMPLES
Issue a local client mTLS bundle:
.PP
.EX
sudo install -d -o custodia -g custodia -m 0700 /tmp/custodia-client-alice
sudo -u custodia custodia-admin \\
  --server-url https://localhost:8443 \\
  --cert /etc/custodia/admin.crt \\
  --key /etc/custodia/admin.key \\
  --ca /etc/custodia/ca.crt \\
  client issue \\
  --signer-url https://localhost:9444 \\
  --client-id client_alice \\
  --out-dir /tmp/custodia-client-alice
sudo chown -R "$USER:$USER" /tmp/custodia-client-alice
.EE
.SH VERSION
Custodia version: @VERSION@
.br
Build commit: @COMMIT@
.br
Build date: @DATE@
.PP
Runtime version is available with:
.PP
.EX
custodia-admin version
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime or API failure.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR custodia-client (1),
.BR custodia-server (1),
.BR custodia-signer (1)
